Endpoint: POST /authentication
Summary: Get auth token
Description: Before a new fidentity process can be started or data from an existing process can be read, the client must authenticate itself. Consider to reuse the token for multiple requests because this endpoint is strictly rate limited.
Tags: Authentication
Request Body: {
  "description": "authentication object that needs to be created",
  "required": true,
  "content": {
    "application/json": {
      "schema": {
        "$ref": "#/components/schemas/authentication"
      }
    }
  }
}
Response 201: created
Response 401: not authenticated
Response 500: general error

Endpoint: POST /fidentity
Summary: Create a new fidentity process
Description: With this service you can start a new fidentity processes.
Tags: fidentity
Request Body: {
  "content": {
    "application/json": {
      "schema": {
        "$ref": "#/components/schemas/input"
      }
    }
  }
}
Response 201: success
Response 401: not authenticated
Response 404: not found
Response 405: Invalid input
Response 500: general error

Endpoint: POST /fidentity/resetCustomer/{extId}
Summary: Reset a fidentity process and Customer
Description: With this service you can reset a existing fidentity process and the associated process with the help of the extId. The Body of the POST Request is empty
Tags: fidentity
Request Body: {
  "content": {
    "application/json": {
      "schema": {}
    }
  }
}
Response 200: success
Response 401: not authenticated
Response 404: not found
Response 405: Invalid input
Response 500: general error

Endpoint: POST /fidentity/process-scan/{processStep}/{extId}
Summary: Process scanned images
Description: With this service you can send scanned images for a fidentity process by the extId.
Tags: fidentity
Request Body: {
  "content": {
    "application/json": {
      "schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "images"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "images": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "object",
              "required": [
                "data",
                "mimetype"
              ],
              "properties": {
                "data": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "format": "binary",
                  "title": "The image data (base64)",
                  "example": "<base 64 string>"
                },
                "mimetype": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "title": "The image mimetype",
                  "example": "image/png"
                },
                "id": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "title": "An image id (optional)"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
Response 200: success
Response 401: not authenticated
Response 404: not found
Response 405: Invalid input
Response 500: general error

